studyArms.name: ABBV-951 Treatment Arm
studyArms.description: All subjects receive an oral loading dose of LD+DDCI followed by a 24-hour daily continuous subcutaneous infusion (CSCI) of ABBV-951. The dose is individualized and titrated during an Optimization Period to achieve optimal clinical response.

arms.name: ABBV-951 Treatment Arm
arms.description: All subjects receive an oral loading dose of LD+DDCI followed by a 24-hour daily continuous subcutaneous infusion (CSCI) of ABBV-951. The dose is individualized and titrated during an Optimization Period to achieve optimal clinical response.

doseEpochs.dose: Individualized (Starting rate F1 based on baseline LED)
doseEpochs.description: Optimization Period: Weekly adjustments to ABBV-951 and concomitant PD medications to reach optimal clinical response.
Maintenance Period: 48 weeks of continuous infusion at the optimized dose.

epochs.name: Screening Period
epochs.description: 10 to 42 days (up to 90 days), including a 6-day Monitoring Period for PD Diary and wearable device baseline.

epochs.name: Optimization Period
epochs.description: Weeks 1-4 (Days 1-28); dose titration of ABBV-951 and adjustment of concomitant PD medications.

epochs.name: Maintenance Period
epochs.description: Weeks 5-52 (Days 29-364); continuous infusion at stable optimal dose.

epochs.name: Follow-up
epochs.description: 30-day follow-up call after the end of infusion for subjects not entering the extension study.
